column12: Set in post-war Seoul, the protagonist, Sonya, works at an American military base as a prostitute. The film comments on the reality of life after the Korean War and the presence of American military bases in South Korea. The film notably has a military base setting, focus on Korean prostitutes, explore the value placed on American goods (e.g., beer, music), and the black market established for these products. These notes highlight the intersections of war, economic struggle, and the interactions between Korean citizens and American soldiers.
